21/03/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The parliamentary committee on rules of procedures decided on Thursday (20 March) that, during all sessions, the chairpersons of all committees in parliament will speak Macedonian. 
Under the constitution, Macedonian is the official language of state institutions. 
Parliament members fluent in other languages, spoken by at least 20 per cent of the population, can use these languages in their own discussions and in speeches to parliament.
In other news Thursday, nearly 2,000 ethnic Albanians protested in Tetovo, demanding the release of two former National Liberation Army members. 
Krenar Osmani and Ibrahim Suleimani were sentenced to six and 15 years in prison respectively for atrocities committed during the 2001 military conflict. 
(Dnevnik, Vest - 21/03/03; MIA, A1 TV - 20/03/03)
